January 19, 1925
Dear Bab,
Just a line to tell you again how much I got out of my visit with you.  It has given me something satisfying and very very fine.
Another fine round at Pittsburg and the lecture went splendidly.  I am staying over here today and going to New York tonight.  The visit to Indianapolis and in particular the unclear  walking with you in that charming little town are like little unclear .  They will stay in my consciousness for the rest of my life. 
S. A.

Thursday night
Dear Bab -
I have crept away from everyone tonight and am in my room - going to bed in a few minutes - very weary. It is the first time I have escaped from people for days - except to fall exhausted into bed.
And yet I have enjoyed it all.  Something has happened to me since I was here before.  Am I more  unclear to people or am I wiser?  For some reason I do not understand I have suddenly found myself able to accept the
